The epic has been written to `/home/stephan/src/FairEmail/docs/epics/2.7-folder-colors-and-per-folder-unread-counters.md`. It covers:

- **Folder color rendering** in both the folder list (vertical color stripe) and navigation pane (icon tinting), including the Inbox-to-account-color fallback and default Trash/Junk warning colors
- **Per-folder unread counters** with bold/highlight styling, numeric display, and the "unexposed" (newly arrived) indicator
- **Child-folder aggregation** when parent folders are collapsed
- **Count-unread flag** controlling contribution to account-level badge totals
- **Hide-when-read** auto-hiding of folders with no unread mail
- **Navigation pane count settings** (unread count, message count, pinned count, drafts total)
- **Sort unread atop** folder ordering option
- Clearly scoped relationship to the existing coloring epic (1.8), with overlap noted in Open Questions
